## Mask<W> trait impls on Mask64 / Mask256 (deferred)

The `arvo-mask-contracts::Mask<const W: u8>` const trait was declared
during round 202604271346 with the intent that `arvo-bitmask::Mask64`
implement `Mask<64>` and `Mask256` implement `Mask<256>`. Round
202604280034's doc CL committed to closing the design-drift gap; the
source side discovered the impl is not mechanical:

- The trait is `pub const trait`, requiring `impl const` impls.
- `Mask64` / `Mask256` inherent methods are non-const today
  (`insert` / `remove` take `&mut self`); functional `set` / `clear`
  shapes need a parallel set of methods or a const-conversion of the
  inherent surface.
- `full()` and `mask_for_width(n)` have no inherent equivalent and
  need to be added.

Tracked here for a follow-up round. Two work blocks:

1. Const-convert (or write parallel const-fn equivalents for) the
   inherent surface covering `set`, `clear`, `test`, `count`,
   `union`, `intersection`, `difference`, `complement`, plus add
   `full` and `mask_for_width(n)`.
2. Wire `impl const Mask<64> for Mask64` and `impl const Mask<256>
   for Mask256` delegating to step 1.

Until this lands, generic-over-`Mask<W>` consumer code finds no
implementor and binds to `Mask64` / `Mask256` concretely.

