## Benchmark round

Exhaustive comparison of arvo types vs raw `f32` / `f64` / `u32` /
`u64` across add / sub / mul / div / sqrt / recip and chain lengths
1 / 4 / 16 / 64, per strategy. Purpose: prove arvo types add no
overhead beyond the strategy's intended cost. Any unexpected overhead
is a bug to fix, not accept. Scope: its own round once the substrate
is green.

## Post-review notes

Items surfaced during a post-shipping review of the substrate; kept
here for future rounds to pick up.

- Cap upper-bound enforcement. Cap(pub USize) lacks any cap on the
  inner USize; constructing Cap(USize(usize::MAX)) is silently legal
  even though array-sized-at-N would fail to compile or exhaust the
  stack. A future round should consider non-pub inner fields with a
  constructor that enforces a pragmatic ceiling (roughly 2^24 as a
  stack-array ceiling under modern OS stack sizes). Ties into
  ConstParamTy newtype hygiene.
- cap_size duplication. The cap_size helper is defined separately in
  arvo-bitmask/src/matrix.rs and arvo-spectral/src/matrix.rs. Resolve
  to a single definition when Matrix promotes into arvo-sparse (the
  Matrix-in-arvo-sparse item in arvo-spectral's BACKLOG). Both copies
  are identical today; the duplication is a promotion artefact.
- StrictFloat::sqrt no_std correctness. The 7-ULP Newton-Raphson
  approximation used by sqrt_f32 / sqrt_f64 violates the bit-exact
  IEEE 754 contract StrictFloat promises. The approximation is
  acceptable for current consumer surfaces (spectral partitioning
  Fiedler-vector sign inspection, no bit-exact dependence). Integrate
  libm or musl-math when a consumer actually depends on
  correctly-rounded sqrt in no_std. An std-gated path is rejected —
  arvo's no_std discipline is absolute.
- Wrapping div-by-zero semantic. Hot / Warm / Cold wrapping div
  returns the numerator unchanged when the divisor is zero. Wrapping
  has no identity for zero; silent garbage is strictly preferable to
  a panic under the Hot / Warm single-instruction discipline. If a
  consumer surfaces a need for a different sentinel (e.g. zero), add
  a checked_div variant rather than change the existing contract.
- Const-generic bit accessors. The three free const fns in
  strategy.rs (ibits_u8, fbits_u8, is_fractional) return raw u8 /
  usize so IBits / FBits values can appear inside anonymous
  const-generic expressions where direct field access is disallowed
  on the current nightly. Tracked via allow-bare-numeric annotations
  pointing at Task #71. Collapse into a single Bits newtype method
  (e.g. const fn Bits::as_u8(self) -> u8) once nightly loosens
  struct-construction rules in const args. No timeline — gated on
  upstream rustc.

